title: Rollins Stock Rating Upgraded by Zacks
text: Subscribe Rollins Stock Rating Upgraded by Zacks Zacks upgraded shares of Rollins from a sell rating to a hold rating in a research note issued to investors last week. September 18, 2015 Zacks upgraded shares of Rollins from a sell rating to a hold rating in a research note issued to investors on Tuesday, AnalystRatings.Net reports . Rollins last posted its earnings results on Wednesday, July 29th. The company reported $0.21 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, meeting the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.21. During the same quarter in the prior year, the company posted $0.28 EPS. The company had revenue of $392.20 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $389.02 million. Rollins’s revenue was up 6.2% on a year-over-year basis. On average, equities research analysts expect that Rollins will post $0.71 earnings per share for the current fiscal year.
